                	<h2 class="page-title">Secure communications with Open Source PKI</h2>
                <!-- start main content -->
    <div class="entry"> 
   
  <ul class="list-ul">
<li> <a href="http://fscons.org/2008/speakers/?action=speaker&amp;id=93">Eklund, Johan</a> and  <a href="http://fscons.org/2008/speakers/?action=speaker&amp;id=101">Wickenberg, Tham </a>are coming to <a href="../../index.html">FSCONS</a> to present: <a href="http://fscons.org/2008/events/?action=event&amp;id=98">Secure communications with Open Source PKI</a></li>
</ul>
<p>PKI used to be reserved to 'Big Corp' and '.gov', but the open source tools have matured over the years and are now available for everyone. In this presentation we want to show how PKI works and how you could benefit from it.</p>
<ul>
<li>When is Public Key Infrastructure useful and when should it be avoided?</li>
<li>What is Public Key Infrastructure and how does it work?</li>
</ul>
<p>We will demonstrate how certificates can be used in common applications  like</p>
<ul>
<li>Firefox: SSL client authentication to an Apache web server</li>
<li>Thunderbird: SMIME email signing and encryption</li>
<li>OpenVPN: Authentication in a virtual private network</li>
<li>Ant: Codesigning jar-files</li>
</ul>
   
  <p class="info">Posted in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_1 first last"><a href="http://fscons.org/2008/taxonomy/term/1" rel="tag" title="uncategorized">Uncategorized</a></li>
</ul> <ul class="links inline"><li class="blog_usernames_blog first"><a href="http://fscons.org/2008/blog/6" title="Read hesa&#039;s latest blog entries.">hesa&#039;s blog</a></li>
<li class="comment_forbidden last"><span><a href="http://fscons.org/2008/user/login?destination=comment%2Freply%2F79%23comment-form">Login</a> to post comments</span></li>
</ul></p>
   <small>Submitted by hesa on Thu, 10/09/2008 - 11:27</small>
   
